    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This collection is made up of three folders containing the papers related to patents of Charles Adler, Jr., ranging from 1936 to 1952. There are letters and sketches, as well as patents for aircraft lights, proximity lights, and safety horns.</field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">Charles Adler, Jr. was an inventor and engineer born in 1899 in Baltimore, Maryland. He attended John Hopkins University and briefly joined the army. Later he joined the Maryland and Pennsylvania Railroad and there developed safety devices. In 1928 he designed the first audible traffic horn. He was granted over 60 patents in his lifetime, 10 of which he donated to the government. He was a member of the Maryland State Aviation Commission and the Maryland Traffic Safety Commission.</field>
